ndex.htm',2000,'July','','English','','General - Network Design and Information','Security','','Network Operations Center','attrib-noncommercial','Administrative Account','    *  Students will be able to:\r\n          o Track complaints/faults/issues raised by customers, by building and using a req/www ticketing system\r\n          o Detect faults as soon as they occur, by building a basic monitoring system using Nocol or equivalent\r\n          o Monitor resources (e.g. bandwidth, temperature, CPU) to catch problems before they become serious\r\n          o Perform netflow analysis\r\n          o Communicate with providers, peers and customers\r\n          o Document all of the important contact numbers and passwords in a readily-accessible format\r\n          o Store and keep track of router configurations and inventory\r\n          o Use an SNMP/TFTP based tool\r\n          o Fix network problems when devices are unreachable\r\n          o Build an OOB serial box\r\n',NULL,NULL,NULL,'Y','4113718740074bfee12d4','2004-01-16 10:27:31','Administrative Account','2004-01-15 18:27:31',NULL,'N'),(30,0,15,6,'Exchange points, route servers and routing registries','Abha Ahuja','http://www.isocws.isoc.org/inet2000/t2/80-xp-irr/index.htm',2000,'July','','English','','Routing','','','Exchange Points/IXPs','attrib-noncommercial','Administrative Account','*  Topics include:\r\n          o What they are.\r\n          o Why you have them (shared medium versus P2P mesh)\r\n          o \\\"Table manners\\\" (don\\\'t point default route/statics, don\\\'t spoof)\r\n          o Politics; nobody is obliged to peer\r\n          o Design: don\\\'t go multisite unless you have enough free bandwidth\r\n',NULL,NULL,NULL,'Y','79798261740074d4111a91','2004-01-16 10:33:00','Administrative Account','2004-01-15 18:33:00',NULL,'N'),(31,0,15,6,'BGP Recap','Philip Smith','',2000,'July','','English','','BGP','Routing','','','attrib-noderivs-noncommercial','Administrative Account','Available in both 