44400766fcef28e','2004-01-16 12:22:36','Administrative Account','2004-01-15 20:22:36',NULL,'N'),(37,0,15,6,'Applying for an AS Number','Paul Gampe','',2000,'July','','English','','Routing','','','','attrib-noncommercial','Administrative Account','This presentation is available in both 1-up and 6-up format in PDF.\r\n\r\nPractical discussion of applying for an AS Number, including an example using the APNIC request form - 17 slides total.',NULL,NULL,NULL,'Y','199548367240076841c5e3c','2004-01-16 12:28:08','Administrative Account','2004-01-15 20:28:08',NULL,'N'),(38,0,15,6,'BGP Route Filtering and Advanced Features practical lab','Cisco Systems','',2000,'July','','English','','BGP','Routing','','','attrib-noderivs-noncommercial','Administrative Account','This practical lab presents BGP route filtering and advanced features, including various configuration methods on BGP peerings to demonstrate neighbor filterings and more advanced IOS features. ',NULL,NULL,NULL,'Y','16457666654007695e30c21','2004-01-16 12:32:44','Administrative Account','2004-01-15 20:32:44',NULL,'N'),(39,0,15,6,'BGP Multihoming','Philip Smith','',2000,'July','','English','','BGP','Routing','','','attrib-noderivs-noncommercial','Administrative Account','Presentation available in 1-up and 6-up format in PDF.',NULL,NULL,NULL,'Y','70841267840076cb2bbfd5','2004-01-16 12:47:25','Administrative Account','2004-01-15 20:47:25',NULL,'N'),(40,0,15,6,'BGP Communities, Transit and Collocation','Philip Smith','',2000,'July','','English','','BGP','Routing','','','attrib-noderivs-noncommercial','Administrative Account','Presentation available in both 1-up and 6-up formats in PDF.',NULL,NULL,NULL,'Y','197041745940076efd6dc44','2004-01-16 12:56:52','Administrative Account','2004-01-15 20:56:52',NULL,'N'),(41,0,15,6,'Interconnection Strategies for ISPs','Bill Norton','',2000,'July','','English','','General - Network Design and Information','Routing','','','attrib-noncommercial','Administrative Account','This presentation is available in both 1-up and 6-up format in PDF. In addition the original paper on which this presenation is based is included with these materials.',NULL,NULL,NULL,'Y','1520135397400770d1b79ef','2004-01-16 13:06:41','Administrative Account','2004-01-15 21:06:41',NULL,'N'),(42,0,15,6,'Peering Decision Tree','Bill Norton','',2000,'July','','English','','General - Network Design and Information','Routing','','','attrib-noderivs-noncommercial','Administrative Account','This presentation is available in 1-up and 6-up format in PDF. The presentation is based on the accompanying paper, \\\"Internet Service Providers and Peering\\\" by Bill Norton.\r\n\r\n-\r\n\r\nHere is part of the abstract for the paper:\r\n\r\n-\r\n\r\nInternet Service Provider (ISP) peering has emerged as one of the most important and effective ways for ISPs to improve the efficiency of operation. Peering is defined as  an interconnection business relationship whereby ISPs provide connectivity to each others  transit customers.  ISPs seek peering relationships primarily for two reasons. First, peering decreases the cost and reliance on purchased Internet transit. As the single greatest operating expense, ISPs seek to minimize these telecommunications costs. Second, peering lowers inter-Autonomous System (AS) traffic latency. By avoiding a transit provider hop in between ISPs traffic between peering ISPs has lower latency. ',NULL,NULL,NULL,'Y','212115105340077316b7cd4','2004-01-16 13:15:05','Administrative Account','2004-01-15 21:15:05',NULL,'N'),(43,0,15,6,'The RIPE Database and Internet Routing Registry','Ambrose Magee','http://www.isocws.isoc.org/inet2000/t5/Ambrose/html/rpsl-db-intro-inet2000/index.htm',2000,'July','','English','','General - Network Design and Information','Routing','','','attrib-noncommercial','Administrative Account','A description and practical guide to the use of the RIPE database for NIC\\\'s and NOC\\\'s.',NULL,NULL,NULL,'Y','212075259540077494cda78','2004-01-16 13:20:40'