INSERT INTO `workshop` VALUES (8,1,'African Network Operators Group (AfNOG) 1','2000-05-01','2000-05-05','http://www.ws.afnog.org/afnog2000/','http://www.afnog.org/2000/','za','Cape Town','Africa','','','English','French','Portuguese','','Graduate School of Business, University of Cape Town','AFNOG Coordinating Office','contact@afnog.org','In conjunction with the inaugural meeting of African Network Operators Group (AfNOG) in May 2000, AfNOG held a Network Technology Workshop prior to the meeting. The workshop took place in facilities of the Graduate School of Business, University of Cape Town, South Africa,from 30 April to 5 May 2000. The workshop offered advanced training to operators of existing African Internet Service Providers (ISPs) who are participants in the process of developing and enhancing a national Internet with regional and international connectivity.\r\n\r\n\r\nAttendance at the workshop included attendance at AfNOG&#039;s inaugural meeting, AfNOG 2000, and  the introductory meeting of AfriNIC (www.afrinic.org), which also was held in Cape Town on 6 May 2000 and 7 May 2000 respectively, following the workshop. ',2000,'May','Y','/var/www/html/data/2000/','2020-12-11 03:11:38','William Hervey Allen','2007-05-26 05:19:33','admin@ws.edu.isoc.org','N','yes','no','no',0,0,-33.925838,18.423220),(2,6,'African Network Operators Group (AfNOG) 2','2001-05-05','2001-05-13','http://www.ws.afnog.org/afnog2001/','http://www.afnog.org/2001/','gh','Accra','Africa','','','English','French','','','Miklin Hotel, East Legon, Accra','AFNOG Coordinating Office','contact@afnog.org','In conjunction with the second  meeting of African Network Operators Group (AfNOG) in May 2001, AfNOG is holding a Network Technology Workshop prior to the meeting.  The workshop will be held in facilities of the Miklin Hotel, East Legon, Accra Ghana, during May 05 - May 13, 2001. The workshop will offer advanced training to operators of existing African Internet Service Providers (ISPs) who are participants in the process of developing and enhancing a national Internet with regional and international connectivity.\r\n\r\nAttendance at the workshop includes attendance at AfNOG&#039;s second meeting, AfNOG 2001 (www.afnog.org), and the second  meeting of AfriNIC (www.afrinic.org), which will be held in Accra on May 12th and 13th  respectively, following the workshop.\r\n\r\nThis workshop builds upon the experiences of the inaugural AfNOG workshop held in Cape Town, South Africa and the INET workshops held during 1993-2000 at eight  locations around the world. ',2001,'May','Y','/var/www/html/data/2001/','2020-12-11 03:11:42','Administrative Account','2007-05-26 05:20:49','admin@ws.edu.isoc.org','N','yes','no','no',0,0,5.556020,-0.196900),(4,8,'South Asian Network Operations Group (SANOG) - I','2003-01-23','2003-01-28','http://www.sanog.org/sanog1/index.html',NULL,'NP','Kathmandu','Asia/Australia/Pacific','','','English','','','Nepali','','Gaurab Raj Upadhaya','<gaurab@wlink.com.np>','The first SANOG meeting was held in conjuction with the CAN IT Conference 2003, a national IT conference organised by the Computer Association of Nepal since 2001. ',2003,'January','Y','/var/www/html/data/2003/','2020-12-11 03:11:47','Steven Huter','2003-10-10 02:39:12',NULL,'N','yes','no','no',0,0,27.701691,85.320602),(5,8,'South Asian Network Operators Group (SANOG) - II','2003-07-20','2003-07-26','http://www.netsa.org.lk/',NULL,'LK','Colombo','Asia/Australia/Pacific','','','English','','','','','Gihan Dihas','netsa@mail.ac.lk','Networking South Asia is hosted by the Lanka Education and Research\r\nNetwork, (LEARN) and co-hosted by the Licensed Internet Service\r\nProviders\' Association (LISPA). Training programmes and meetings are\r\norganized by SANOG and APAN, and the Asia Pacific Network Information\r\nCentre (APNIC).\r\n',2003,'July','Y','/var/www/html/data/2003/','2020-12-11 03:11:51','Steven Huter','2003-10-10 02:50:25',NULL,'N','yes','no','no',0,0,6.935480,79.848679),(6,8,'African Network Operators Group (AfNOG) 4','2003-06-08','2003-06-13','http://www.ws.afnog.org/afnog2003/','http://www.afnog.org/2003/','UG','Kampala','Africa','','','English','French','','','Hotel Africana','Badru Ntege','ntegeb@one2net.co.ug','In conjunction with the fourth meeting of African Network Operators Group (AfNOG) in June 2003, AfNOG is holding a Network Technology Workshop prior to the meeting. The workshop will be held in facilities of the Hotel Africana, Kampala,Uganda during June 08 -June 13, 2003. The workshop will offer advanced training to operators of existing African Internet Service Providers (ISPs) who are participants in the process of developing and enhancing a national Internet with regional and international connectivity. Attendance at the workshop includes attendance at AfNOG&#039;s fourth meeting, AfNOG 2003, and the fourth of AfriNIC (www.afrinic.org), which will be held in Kampala on June 14th-15th, following the workshop. This workshop builds upon the experiences of the previous AfNOG workshops held in Cape Town, , Accra, Lome and the INET workshops held during 1993-2000 at eight locations around the world.',2003,'June','Y','/var/www/html/data/2003/','2020-12-11 03:11:56','Steven Huter','2007-05-26 05:29:52','admin@ws.edu.isoc.org','N','yes','no','no',0,0,0.316280,32.582191),(7,8,'African Network Operators Group (AfNOG) 3','2002-05-05','2002-05-10','http://ws.afnog.org/afnog2002/','http://www.afnog.org/2002/','TG','Lome','Africa','','','French','English','','','Mercure Hotel, Sarakawa','Alain Aina','aalain@trstech.net','There are three workshop tracks, covering the topics outlined below.\r\n\r\nTRACK 1. SCALABLE INTERNET SERVICES\r\n\r\nWho should attend: Technical staff who are now providing mail, file, web, and other TCP/IP based services to local and/or dial-up end users.\r\n\r\nPrerequisites: UNIX use and some Unix system administration.\r\n\r\nSubjects: large-scale provision of UNIX-based TCP/IP services such as:\r\n\r\n    * DNS (Domain Name Service)\r\n    * SMTP mail exchange\r\n    * POP mail delivery\r\n    * Mailing lists\r\n    * HTTP web service\r\n    * Security\r\n\r\nTRACK 2. SCALABLE NETWORK INFRASTRUCTURE\r\n\r\nWho should attend: Technical staff who are now operating a wide area TCP/IP network, likely with international and/or multi-provider connectivity. Those who will be involved in the establishment and/or operation of a basic national network infrastructure in the country.\r\n\r\nPrerequisites: experience using TCP/IP-based networking technologies.\r\n\r\nSubjects: configuration and operation of larger scale backbones, including:\r\n\r\n    * Basic routing\r\n    * OSPF routing\r\n    * BGP routing (limited)\r\n    * Management of router    \r\n      configuration\r\n    * NOC (Network Operation Center)\r\n    * Exchange points between \r\n      networks\r\n    * Security\r\n\r\nTRACK 3. FRENCH TRACK ( same as Track 2)\r\n\r\n    * Base des reseaux IP\r\n    * Bases de configuration des \r\n      routeurs Cisco\r\n    * Routage statique (utilisation         d&#039;Unix et de Routeur Cisco)\r\n    * OSPF\r\n    * Architecture d&#039;un reseau \r\n      redondant\r\n    * BGP\r\n    * NOC services et application\r\n    * Securite Reseau\r\n\r\n',2002,'May','Y','/var/www/html/data/2002/','2020-12-11 03:12:00','Steven Huter','2007-05-26 05:22:01','admin@ws.edu.isoc.org','N','yes','no','no',0,0,6.128740,1.221540),(10,6,'INET 1999: Network Training Workshop','1999-06-13','1999-06-20','http://www.isocws.isoc.org/inet99/','','us','San Jose','North America','','','English','French','','','San Jose State University','','','The primary goal of this Workshop is to empower participants from\r\ndeveloping countries to return to their countries and introduce,\r\nextend, use and manage their publicly accessible national Internets\r\nfor the benefit of the economic and social development of their\r\ncountry.  The Workshop seeks to provide the knowledge to allow\r\npeople to do this so that all sectors of activity in developing\r\ncountries can benefit from the effective access to resource and\r\nexpertise that the Internet can provide so well.',1999,'June','Y','/var/www/html/data/1999/','2020-12-11 03:12:05','Administrative Account','2004-01-12 11:20:49',NULL,'N','yes','no','no',0,0,37.339390,-121.894958),(11,6,'INET 1998: Network Training Workshop','1998-07-12','1998-07-19','http://www.isocws.isoc.org/inet98/','','ch','Geneva','Europe','','','English','French','','','Cite Universitaire','','','The primary goal of this Workshop is to empower participants from\r\ndeveloping countries to return to their countries and introduce,\r\nextend, use and manage their publicly accessible national Internets\r\nfor the benefit of the economic and social development of their\r\ncountry.  The Workshop seeks to provide the knowledge to allow\r\npeople to do this so that all sectors of activity in developing\r\ncountries can benefit from the effective access to resource and\r\nexpertise that the Internet can provide so well.',1998,'July','Y','/var/www/html/data/1998/','2020-12-11 03:12:09','Administrative Account','2004-01-12 11:25:20',NULL,'N','yes','no','no',0,0,46.202221,6.145690),(12,6,'INET 1997: Network Training Workshop','1997-06-12','1997-06-22','http://www.isocws.isoc.org/inet97/','','my','Kuala Lumpur','Asia/Australia/Pacific','','','English','','','','Petronas Permata Training Center','','','The primary goal of this Workshop is to empower participants from\r\ndeveloping countries to return to their countries and introduce,\r\nextend, use and manage their publicly accessible national Internets\r\nfor the benefit of the economic and social development of their\r\ncountry.  The Workshop seeks to provide the knowledge to allow\r\npeople to do this so that all sectors of activity in developing\r\ncountries can benefit from the effective access to resource and\r\nexpertise that the Internet can provide so well.',1997,'June','Y','/var/www/html/data/1997/','2020-12-11 03:12:14','Administrative Account','2004-01-12 11:28:35',NULL,'N','yes','no','no',0,0,3.141200,101.686531),(13,6,'INET 1996: Network Training Workshop','1996-06-16','1996-06-22','http://www.isocws.isoc.org/inet96/','','ca','Montreal','North America','','','English','French','','','McGill University','','','The goals of the workshop are:\r\n\r\n\r\n1. To train a critical mass of trainer/professionals in network infrastructure, transport, services, and management to be able to support an extension of meaningful Internet-related activities within the countries represented.\r\n\r\n\r\n2. To identify and share individual and institutional contacts as well as information sources that will assist the process of national development, using international Internet connections.\r\n\r\n\r\n3. To build robust professional linkages between all participants in the programs so that the mentor-student and colleague-colleague relationships formed during the workshop and conferences will remain strong and of continuing usefulness well beyond the workshop and conference.\r\n\r\n\r\n4. To increase the level of cooperation among existing projects and activities for establishing data networks in developing countries.\r\n\r\n\r\n5. To train people and groups of people who will return to their country and region and who will teach others what they have learned at the workshop. ',1996,'June','Y','/var/www/html/data/1996/','2020-12-11 03:16:28','Administrative Account','2004-01-12 11:34:23',NULL,'N','yes','no','no',0,0,45.508839,-73.587807),(14,6,'INET 1995: Network Training Workshop','1995-06-18','1995-06-24','http://www.isocws.isoc.org/inet95/','','us','Honolulu','North America','Asia/Australia/Pacific','','English','','','','','','','Developing Country Workshop\r\n\r\n\r\nThe Network Training Workshop for Developing Countries will be a week-long program in 18-24 June of intensive instruction, with a hands-on emphasis on Internet set-up, operations, maintenance, and management. The Workshop covers the four program tracks:\r\n\r\n\r\n    * Dial-up Networking Technology\r\n\r\n    * TCP/IP Networking Technology\r\n\r\n    * Network Navigation and Services\r\n\r\n* National Network Management ',1995,'June','Y','/var/www/html/data/1995/','2020-12-11 03:16:32','Administrative Account','2004-01-12 11:38:28',NULL,'N','yes','no','no',0,0,21.306940,-157.858337),(15,6,'INET 2000: Network Training Workshop','2000-07-09','2000-07-15','http://www.isocws.isoc.org/inet2000/','','jp','Yokohama','Asia/Australia/Pacific','','','English','French','','','Keio University - Shonan-Fujisawa Campus','','','The primary goal of this Workshop is to empower participants from\r\ndeveloping countries to return to their countries and introduce,\r\nextend, use and manage their publicly accessible national Internets\r\nfor the benefit of the economic and social development of their\r\ncountry.  The Workshop seeks to provide the knowledge to allow\r\npeople to do this so that all sectors of activity in developing\r\ncountries can benefit from the effective access to resource and\r\nexpertise that the Internet can provide so well.',2000,'July','Y','/var/www/html/data/2000/','2020-12-11 03:16:37','Administrative Account','2004-01-12 11:42:40',NULL,'N','yes','no','no',0,0,35.433331,139.649994),(20,6,'APRICOT 2004 Workshop','2004-02-18','2004-02-22','http://www.apricot2004.net/workshop-desc.asp','http://www.apricot2004.net/default.asp','my','Kuala Lumpur','Asia/Australia/Pacific','','','English','','','','Palace of the Golden Horses hotel in Kuala Lumpur, Malaysia','Molly Cheam Molly and Lay Tiong','secretariat@apricot2004.net','APRICOT (Asia Pacific Regional INTERNET Conference on Operational Technologies) is a forum that facilitates knowledge sharing among Internet builders in the Asia Pacific region, with peers and leaders from the Internet community worldwide.\r\n\r\nAPRICOT was first held in 1996, and is now the major annual Internet operations conference of this region. It is also the only such conference which operates on a non-profit basis for the benefit of Internet development in the Asia Pacific.\r\n\r\nA recently added feature of APRICOT, building on a very successful pilot at APRICOT 2001, is to offer attendees the opportunity of attending hands on workshops in major technology areas pertinent to the ISP industry. \r\n\r\nTopics On Offer\r\n\r\n1. Routing Workshop\r\nIntroduction to OSPF and BGP, Introduction to BGP policy, Router Configuration Essentials, BGP Route Reflectors, Policy Routing. Participants should bring their own laptop if they have one.\r\n\r\n2. BGP Multihoming Workshop\r\nIntroduction to BGP, BGP Multihoming basics, More advanced multihoming practices, Case Study. Participants should bring their own laptop if they have one.\r\n\r\n3. DNS Workshop\r\nSystem fundamentals, Basic DNS (Server, Client, Dynamic Update, Upgrading, Adding Zones, Using Slaves), Advanced DNS (IPv6, DNSSEC, AD integration). Participants may bring their own Linux/BSD based laptop if they have one.\r\n\r\n4. ISP Security Workshop\r\nIntroduction to network security, System Security, Network Security, Dealing with DOS attacks.\r\n\r\n5. Network Management Workshop\r\nEvolution of Internet infrastructure, structure of the Internet, IP routing, Multi-Provider Issues, Peering, Capacity Management and Planning, Business and Pricing Models, Network Operations Management, Security, DNS, IP Address Registries. Participants may bring their own Linux/BSD based laptop if they have one.\r\n\r\n6. IPv6 Routing Workshop\r\nSimilar to the Routing Workshop, but using IPv6. Topics include Introduction to IGPs and BGP, Introduction to BGP policy, Router Configuration Essentials, and BGP Route Reflectors. Participants should bring their own laptop if they have one. ',2004,'February','Y','/var/www/html/data/2004/','2020-12-11 03:16:41','Administrative Account','2004-02-21 08:42:35','admin@ws.edu.isoc.org','N','yes','no','no',0,0,3.141200,101.686531),(17,6,'AIT/Internet2 Multicast Workshop','2003-05-18','2003-05-20','http://irl.cs.ait.ac.th/multicast_workshop.html','','th','Pathumthani','Asia/Australia/Pacific','','','English','Thai','','','AIT Conference Center, Asian Institute of Technology','Ms. Patcharee Basu, Kanchana Kanchanasut, Steven Huter','yoo@cs.ait.ac.th, Kanchana.Kanchanasut@ait.ac.th, sghuter@nsrc.org','Topics covered at this workshop included:\r\n\r\n    * Router Configuration\r\n    * Multicast addressing\r\n    * Protocol Soup\r\n          o IGMP (Internet Group Membership Protocol) used by hosts and routers to tell each other about group membership\r\n          o PIM-SM (Protocol Independent Multicast - Sparse Mode) used to propagate forwarding state between routers.\r\n          o SSM (Source Specific Multicast) utilizes a subset of PIM\'s functionality to guaranty source-only trees in the 232/8 range.\r\n          o MSDP (Multicast Source Discovery Protocol) used to exchange ASM active source information between RPs.\r\n          o MBGP (Multiprotocol BGP) used to exchange routing information for interdomain RPF checking.\r\n    * SSM & other topics\r\n    * Deploying multicast in a multi-vendor environment',2003,'May','Y','/var/www/html/data/2003/','2020-12-11 03:16:46','Administrative Account','2004-01-18 22:31:02',NULL,'N','yes','no','no',0,0,14.045540,100.639549),(18,8,'South Asian Network Operators Group (SANOG) - III','2004-01-15','2004-01-22','http://www.sanog.org/sanog3/program.html','http://ipv6forum.org.in/events/jan2004/','IN','Bangalore','Asia/Australia/Pacific','','','English','','','','','Gaurab Raj Upadhaya','gaurab@lahai.com','',2004,'January','Y','/var/www/html/data/2004/','2020-12-11 03:16:51','Steven Huter','2004-01-28 09:02:52',NULL,'N','yes','no','no',0,0,12.971940,77.593689),(19,8,'CEDIA Network Training Workshop - IP Services and Network Security','2004-02-29','2004-03-06','http://www.cedia.edu.ec/','http://ws.edu.isoc.org/workshops/2004/CEDIA/curiculum.html#detallado','EC','