a. NANOG will meet as usual from Sunday to Tuesday, and ARIN from Wednesday to Friday.\r\n\r\nTutorials will begin on Sunday afternoon, Oct. 17, at 1:30 p.m. The General Session begins at 9:00 a.m. on Oct. 18, and ends at approximately 4:00 p.m. on Tuesday, Oct. 19. Registration begins August 23, and the fee is $350.\r\n\r\nARIN XIV\r\n---------\r\nOctober 20-22, 2004, in Reston, Virginia, will be held back-to-back with NANOG 32. The meetings will be held at the Hyatt Reston Town Center, a short drive from Dulles International Airport, with Washington D.C. only minutes away.\r\n\r\nMeeting Registration Form\r\n\r\nHotel Information\r\n\r\nOn Sunday, October 17, during NANOG 32, ARIN staff will hold a tutorial providing a general overview of ARIN, and will include details of ARIN services, RIR structure, and how to get involved in ARIN activities. On Monday, October 18, during the evening, there will be a NANOG BoF for ARIN to receive feedback from the operator community. The night of Tuesday, October 19, will include a program of ARIN activities including a Policy Proposal BoF. Wednesday, October 20, will be the first day of the Public Policy Meeting and, that evening, an exciting social event. The second day of the Public Policy Meeting will follow on Thursday, October 21, and the meeting will end on Friday, October 22 with the Members Meeting. ',2004,'October','Y','/var/www/html/data/2004/','2006-01-16 13:14:41','Administrative Account','2004-09-01 17:31:08',NULL,'N','yes','no','no',0,0,0.000000,0.000000),(31,6,'ICANN 2004','2004-12-01','2004-12-05','http://www.icanncapetown.co.za/','http://www.icann.org/','za','Cape Town','Africa','Africa','','English','French','Afrikaans','','Cape Town International Convention Center','','info@icanncapetown.co.za','',2004,'December','Y','/var/www/html/data/2004/','2020-12-17 23:30:34','Administrative Account','2004-09-01 17:37:44',NULL,'N','yes','no','no',0,0,-33.925838,18.423220),(32,6,'18th APNIC Open Policy Meeting','2004-08-