ors, Video, PABX and Telecommunications Engineers and Technicians\r\n\r\nCourse Duration\r\n\r\n1.5 days\r\n\r\nCourse Contents\r\n\r\nThis training covers the followings topics:\r\n- Overview of VoIP\r\n- Overview of SIP\r\n- SIP Express Router (SER)\r\n- Installation and basic configuration of SER Proxy Server\r\n- Building computer-based SIP clients\r\n- Peering SIP Networks\r\n- Auxiliary SIP systems ',2006,'May','Y','/var/www/html/data/2006/','2020-12-18 17:09:13','Administrative Account','2006-06-06 15:41:33',NULL,'N',NULL,'no','no',0,0,13.753980,100.501442),(175,6,'Internet Resource Management - Essentials - APNIC','2006-06-13','2006-06-13','http://www.interlab.ait.ac.th/training/2006/internetresource.html','http://www.interlab.ait.ac.th/contact_us.html','th','Bangkok','Asia/Australia/Pacific','','','English','Thai','','','Training Room, intERLab, AIT, Thailand','','','Objectives:\r\n\r\nTo assists current / prospective APNIC members and other interested parties to request internet resources (IP address, ASN, reverse DNS delegation) the easy way. And also to keep them up-to-date and familiar with the latest policies and procedures.\r\n\r\nWho should attend?\r\n\r\nTechnical personnel who are responsible for allocating and/or assigning IP addresses such as hostmaster employees of network information centers or ISPs, network planners, designers, and network engineers or other interested persons are welcome to attend the Training.',2006,'June','Y','/var/www/html/data/2006/','2020-12-18 17:09:20','Administrative Account','2006-06-06 15:46:10','admin@ws.edu.isoc.org','N',NULL,'no','no',0,0,13.753980,100.501442),(176,6,'APNIC Routing Essentials Workshop','2006-06-14','2006-06-16','http://www.interlab.ait.ac.th/training/2006/apnic-routing.html','http://www.interlab.ait.ac.th/contact_us.html','th','Bangkok','Asia/Australia/Pacific','','','English','','','','  Training Room, intERLab,  AIT, Thailand','','','Objectives:\r\n\r\nThis workshop seeks to achieve the following objectives:\r\n\r\n    * To identify the design requirements in running a network\r\n    * To perform IP addressing best practices for the network infrastructure\r\n    * To configure a router running in a simulated network environment\r\n    * To use appropriate routing protocols that will handle the traffic flow to address the reliability, redundancy, and performance requirements of a network\r\n    * To configure Interior Gateway Protocol (IGP) and ExteriorGateway Protocol (EGP) such as the Open Shortest Path First (OSPF) for IGP and Border Gateway Protocol version 4 (BGPv4) for EGP.\r\n\r\nWho should attend?\r\n\r\nThe targeted audience for this workshop is networking professionals who are responsible for planning, implementing and maintaining the networks.',2006,'June','Y','/var/www/html/data/2006/','2020-12-18 17:09:26','Administrative Account','2006-06-06 15:50:26',NULL,'N',NULL,'no','no',0,0,13.753980,100.501442),(177,6,'AIT Lab: Basic Routing','2006-06-20','2006-06-20','http://www.interlab.ait.ac.th/training/2006/routing.html','http://www.interlab.ait.ac.th/contact_us.html','th','Bangkok','Asia/Australia/Pacific','','','English','','','','Training room, intERLab, AIT, Thailand','','','Objectives\r\n\r\nTo enable participants to perform basic configuring functions for the Internet routing and be able to perform trouble shooting.\r\n\r\nWho should attend?\r\n\r\nNetwork Manager, Network Operators and Network Engineers\r\n\r\nCourse Duration\r\n\r\n3 days\r\n\r\nCourse Contents\r\n\r\nThis training covers the followings topics:\r\n- Router Management\r\n- Security\r\n- Network Management\r\n- RIP Routing Protocol\r\n- OSPF Routing Protocol\r\n- IS-IS Routing Protocol\r\n- BGP Routing Protocol',2006,'June','Y','/var/www/html/data/2006/','2020-12-18 17:09:33','Administrative Account','2006-06-13 19:11:21','admin@ws.edu.isoc.org','N',NULL,'no','no',0,0,13.753980,100.501442),(178,6,'AIT Lab: Basic DNS','2006-08-28','2006-08-29','http://www.interlab.ait.ac.th/training/2006/dns.html','http://www.interlab.ait.ac.th/contact_us.html','th','Bangkok','Asia/Australia/Pacific','','','English','','','','AIT Conference Center, AIT, Thailand','','','Objectives\r\n\r\nProvide the participants with in depth technical information on basic concepts of DNS, configuration and operations.\r\n\r\nWho should attend?\r\n\r\nNetwork engineers, network planners, systems administrators and anyone who is involved in administering Network Operation Centres.\r\n\r\nCourse Duration\r\n\r\n2 days\r\n\r\nCourse Contents\r\n\r\nThis training covers the followings topics:\r\n- DNS concepts\r\n- BIND (DNS server) and Resolver (DNS client) configurations\r\n- DNS debugging tools &amp; troubleshooting\r\n- Reverse DNS ',2006,'August','Y','/var/www/html/data/2006/','2020-12-18 17:09:39','Administrative Account','2006-06-13 19:10:49','admin@ws.edu.isoc.org','N',NULL,'no','no',0,0,13.753980,100.501442),(179,6,'AIT Lab: Advanced Routing','2006-08-30','2006-09-01','http://www.interlab.ait.ac.th/training/2006/adv-routing.html','http://www.interlab.ait.ac.th/contact_us.html','th','Bangkok','Asia/Australia/Pacific','','','English','','','','AIT Conference Center, AIT, Thailand','','','Objectives\r\n\r\nTo enable participants to perform advanced configuring functions and policy based for the Internet routing and be able to perform trouble shooting.\r\n\r\nWho should attend?\r\n\r\nNetwork Manager, Network Operators and Network Engineers\r\n\r\nCourse Duration\r\n\r\n3 days\r\n\r\nCourse Contents\r\n\r\nThis training covers the followings topics:\r\n- Introduction to Internet Routing - IGP setting\r\n- BGP setting\r\n   * IBGP setting\r\n   * EBGP setting\r\n- Multihoming\r\n- Peering\r\n   * private peering\r\n   * paid peering\r\n   * IXP peering\r\n- Case study: ISPs Typical Policy',2006,'August','Y','/var/www/html/data/2006/','2020-12-18 17:09:46','Administrative Account','2006-06-13 19:09:37','admin@ws.edu.isoc.org','N',NULL,'no','no',0,0,13.753980,100.501442),(180,6,'Workshop for TEIN2 NOC Engineers','2006-09-04','2006-09-08','http://www.interlab.ait.ac.th/training/2006/tein2.html','http://www.interlab.ait.ac.th/contact_us.html','th','Bangkok','Asia/Australia/Pacific','','','English','','','',' AIT Conference Center, AIT, Thailand','','','The TEIN2 Workshop is targeted at bringing network operation personnel from the TEIN2 beneficiary countries together and to bring them all to the level qualified for the operation and management of TEIN2 networks. From our successful Kick-Off Workshop held in September 2005, we are convinced that such a face-to-face with hands-on practical sessions is strongly recommended to be held annually.\r\n\r\nAmong the TEIN2 technical NOC teams, we categorize the personnel into 3 categories: Junior Engineers (Group A), Senior Engineers or Network Administrators (Group B) and Technical Managers (Group C).',2006,'September','Y','/var/www/html/data/2006/','2020-12-18 17:09:53','Administrative Account','2006-06-06 16:48:41',NULL,'N',NULL,'no','no',0,0,13.753980,100.501442),(181,6,'Advanced DNS Workshop','2006-12-12','2006-12-15','http://www.interlab.ait.ac.th/training/2006/adv-dns.html','http://www.interlab.ait.ac.th/contact_us.html','th','Bangkok','Asia/Australia/Pacific','','','English','','','',' AIT Conference Center, AIT, Thailand','','','Objectives\r\n\r\nProvide the participants with in depth technical information on advanced concepts of DNS, configuration, operations and security.\r\n\r\nWho should attend?\r\n\r\nNetwork engineers, network planners, systems administrators and anyone who is involved in administering Network Operation Centres.\r\n\r\nCourse Duration\r\n\r\n4 days\r\n\r\nCourse Contents\r\n\r\nThis training covers the followings topics:\r\n- DNS concepts\r\n- BIND (DNS server) and Resolver (DNS client) configurations\r\n- DNS debugging tools &amp; troubleshooting\r\n- Reverse DNS\r\n- ACLs\r\n- Split DNS\r\n- RNDC\r\n- TSIG\r\n- DNSSEC\r\n- Secured dynamic updates ',2006,'Decembe