\n\r\nMaterials\r\n\r\nCD-ROM (1st: Ubuntu installation CD / 2nd: free tools)\r\nPrinted PPT slides Handbook (if there are any from Ubuntu)\r\n\r\nOperating System we will use: Ubuntu (http://www.ubuntu.com)\r\n\r\nContents: (tentative, order can be changed)\r\n\r\n   1. About hardware\r\n      What hardware configuration for what service? Number of CPUs, size of memory, type of RAID, size of hard disks.\r\n      Type of hardware(server type? PC type?)\r\n\r\n   2. Installation of Ubuntu from the CD-ROM\r\n      - Step by step installation\r\n      - Configuration of the network\r\n      - Software RAID\r\n\r\n   3. Tightening the security\r\n      - Introduction of packaging system\r\n      - Installation and configuration of sudo Kernel reconfiguration\r\n      - System upgrade Port upgrade\r\n\r\n   4. Linux administration\r\n      - Adding users step by step\r\n      - Network configuration from the console Other commands used for administration\r\n\r\n   5. How to install and configure a service: example Apache web server\r\n      - Installation Apache Web server is used as an example of setting up a service\r\n        (this workshop won&#039;t go into the details of setting up a web site)\r\n\r\n   6. Remote administration of the server Installation and configuration of ssh Usage of a remote X window client\r\n\r\n   7. Back up and restore\r\n      This part may be limited to demonstration only due to the limitation of available training equipment.\r\n\r\n   8. Troubleshooting Tools (ping, traceroute, tcpdump, wireshark, telnet)\r\n      Boot in single user mode\r\n      Boot process fsck\r\n\r\n   9. Taking logs\r\n      The importance of time synchronization: NTP configuration\r\n      Using and configuring syslog\r\n      Analysis, how to read logs\r\n',2008,'August','Y','/var/www/html/data/2008/','2020-12-18 17:33:31','Administrative Account','2008-07-29 14:20:04',NULL,'N',NULL,'no','no',0,0,13.753980,100.501442),(408,296,'15th Euro-IX Forum','2009-11-02',