cussion and active participation from all attendees. As such, we favor submissions reporting exciting on-going work. ',2009,'April','Y','/var/www/html/data/2009/','2008-09-03 17:49:24','Administrative Account','2008-09-03 10:49:24',NULL,'N',NULL,'no','no',0,0,0.000000,0.000000),(416,6,'NSP: Workshop on Network Security','2008-10-07','2008-10-08','http://www.nsp.org.pk/nspWork/workshopDetails.php','http://www.nsp.org.pk/nspWork/if1O2K3-2.php?uid1=2','pk','Karachi','Asia/Australia/Pacific','','','English','','','','Sheraton Karachi Hotel','','','Workshop Details\r\n\r\nNetwork Security workshop is a highly interactive session and focuses on core security topics such as IOS security, Firewall, IPS, and VPN technologies.\r\n\r\nThe workshop aims at basic-to-intermediate level, laying a basic security foundation that helps networking professionals understand and implement state-of-the-art security technologies and solutions.\r\n\r\nCourse Outline\r\n\r\nFor a 2-days class, the topic coverage is wide but deep enough providing basic concepts and implementation guidelines as well as hands-on configuration skills.\r\n\r\nThe workshop will cover basic understanding of common security products and technologies to protect the network. The workshop will provide hands-on configuration examples, and candidates will be able to demonstrate their understanding using practical configuration scenarios.\r\n\r\nWorkshop Outline\r\n\r\n    * Cisco PIX/ASA Firewall\r\n    * Cisco Intrusion Prevention System (IPS)\r\n    * Three-Planes; Control, Management &amp; Data Plane security\r\n    * CoPP and Infrastructure ACLs\r\n    * Cisco IOS Security features\r\n    * Anti-Spoofing techniques\r\n    * IPsec VPN solutions\r\n    * Site-to-Site (L2L) VPN\r\n    * Dynamic Multipoint VPN (DMVPN)\r\n    * Remote Access VPN\r\n',2008,'October','Y','/var/www/html/data/2008/','2020-12-18 17:34:30','Administrative Account','2008-09-04 14:44:32',NULL,'N',NULL,'no','no',0,0,24.860800,67.010399),(417,6,'NgNOG 2007 Workshop','2007-11-18','2007-11-24','http://www.forum.org.ng/ngNOG/2007Report','','ng','Kano','Africa','','','English','','','','Bayero University Kano','','','ngNOG 2007, the 2nd in the annual series of the Nigerian Network Operators Group (ngNOG) Workshops and Meetings, was successfully held at the Bayero University Kano (BUK) in Kano, from 18-24 November 2007.\r\n\r\nSeventy five (75) delegates from 28 Nigerian Institutions and Organizations (HEIs, ISPs and private firms, NGOs, Government Agencies and Ministries) were trained by 16 volunteer instructors (8 from HEIs and 8 from the private sector) in the five parallel tracks of the 2007 ngNOG workshop in Kano. A healthy, steady growth and diversification of the ngNOG community is already observable. Respectively, 35 delegates from 14 institutions and 56 from 14 institutions participated in one track at pre-ngNOG Ibadan and in three tracks at ngNOG Jos last year.',2007,'November','Y','/var/www/html/data/2007/','2020-12-18 17:34:37','Administrative Account','2008-09-07 19:30:31',NULL,'N',NULL,'no','no',0,0,12.000120,8.516720),(418,6,'NgNOG 2008 Workshop','2008-11-16','2008-11-26','http://www.forum.org.ng/ngnog/2008announcement','http://www.forum.org.ng/ngnog/apply','ng','Lagos','Africa','','','English','','','','Center for Information Technology and Systems,','','','The 2008 Nigerian Network Operators Group Workshops and Meetings, University of Lagos, 16-26 November, 2008\r\n\r\nThe Convenors of the Nigerian Network Operators Group are pleased to announce the 3rd edition of the ngNOG Workshops and Meetings scheduled to take place as follows;\r\n\r\nWorkshop Venue:\r\nCenter for Information Technology and Systems,\r\nUniversity of Lagos\r\n\r\nTime: 9:00am Daily\r\nDate: 17 - 21 November, 2008\r\n\r\nConference Venue:\r\nAfe Babalola Hall, University of Lagos\r\n\r\nTime: 9:00am Daily\r\nDate: 24- 25 November, 2008\r\n\r\nEvent Timetable:\r\nArrival &amp; Registration: 16 November, 2008 (Sunday)\r\nngNOG Workshop: 17 - 21 November, 2008 (Monday - Friday)\r\nngNOG Tutorials: 22 - 23 November, 2008 (Saturday -Sunday)\r\nngNOG Meetings: 24 - 25 November, 2008 (Monday - Tuesday)\r\nDeparture: 26 November, 2008 (Wednesday)\r\n\r\nThis 10 day event is a domestication of the annual AfNOG Workshop on Network Technology (www.afnog.org) and will include two days for meetings and the Annual Conference on ICTs and Education.\r\n\r\nAbout ngNOG\r\nngNOG is a forum for cooperation and the exchange of technical information between operators of Internet-connected networks in Nigeria. For more information please visit http://forum.org.ng/ngnog/about\r\n\r\nngNOG Workshop on Network Technology\r\nngNOG Workshop on Network Technology offers training in Five Parallel Tracks to those who are in the process of developing and enhancing an Internet-connected network with local and international connectivity. The target audience includes mid-level and senior technical staff of research and education networks, public and private networks, commercial Internet Service Providers (ISPs), NGOs and other stakeholders.\r\n\r\nSystem Administration: focused on using a Unix-like operating system as a platform for delivery of Internet services.\r\n\r\nInternet Services: focused on the design and operation of email, web, and other Internet services, in ways that can scale to handle large numbers of end users.\r\n\r\nInternet Infrastructure: focused on the design and operation of networks using routers and switches, in ways that can scale to handle large numbers of interconnected sites.\r\n\r\nEnergy Planning and Appropriate Power Technology: focused on Energy Planning for Networks, backups, and alternative power technologies for networks in energy-challenged environments.\r\n\r\nICT Strategy and Management: focused on Strategies for managing departments and units that provide ICT Services in an organization\r\n\r\nFurther information about the workshop can be found at http://forum.org.ng/ngnog/workshop/2008structure. Application forms can be filled on line at http://forum.org.ng/ngnog/apply.\r\n\r\nInterested applicants should kindly note that applications will be closed on 20th September, 2008.\r\n\r\nngNOG Tutorials\r\nTutorials will be held on 22-23 November, 2008 at the Center for Information Technology and Systems of the University of Lagos.\r\n\r\nTutorials are technical workshops which focus on a particular subject in-depth and are generally non-commercial in nature. Tutorials take place in a classroom-style environment, and may include a hands-on practical component. They are intended to offer advanced training relating to technology and best practices already deployed or soon to be deployed on networking and related services provisioning for ISP operations.\r\n\r\nFor more information about how to apply to teach or present a tutorial please visit http://forum.org.ng/ngnog/tutorials.\r\n\r\n3rd ngNOG Meeting and Conference on ICTs &amp; Education\r\n\r\nThe 3rd ngNOG Conference and Meeting will be held at the Afe Babalola Hall of the University of Lagos on 24-25 November, 2008.\r\n\r\nThe conference is modeled after AfNOG (African Network Operators Group www.afnog.org) conferences and the ICTs and Education Conferences that was initiated by the University of Jos in 2003. The meetings consist of engineering staff from network service providers, managers from IT enterprises, policy makers, regulatory bodies, and senior members and administrators of the research and education community.\r\nPresentations or panel discussions may range in length from 30 minutes to 2 hours.\r\n\r\nThose interested in making a presentation or chairing a panel discussion at the ngNOG meetings are invited to submit a proposal, following the instructions at http://forum.org.ng/ngnog/conference\r\n\r\nPlease note that the closing date for receipt of expressions interest is 20th September, 2008.',2008,'November','Y','/var/www/html/data/2008/','2020-12-18 17:34:44','Administrative Account','2008-09-07 19:33:48',NULL,'N',NULL,'no','no',0,0,6.454070,3.394670),(419,6,'UniForum DNS Training: Introductory and Advanced','2008-09-22','2008-09-26','http://www.coza.net.za/dnsTraining/','','za','CapeTown','Africa','','','English','','','','','','','DNS Introduction - Working Technologies IBM Training Centre, Gazelle Close, Corporate Park, Midrand ‚Äì 22 to 23 September 2008\r\n\r\nDNS Advanced - Autumn Leaf IT, Unit 14, Old Dutch Square, cnr Old Paarl &amp; Bill Bezuidenhout, Bellville, CapeTown ‚Äì 24 to 26 September 2008\r\n\r\nPlease note that places are limited to 18 delegates for each course. Applications are subject to to a R500.00 refundable deposit on attendance. Applications will only be confirmed on receipt of the deposit. Applications will be closed once the total number of deposits have been received. Deposits of delegates that do not attend will forfeited, and in turn donated to the ISPA Teachers Training Program.\r\nDeposits may be paid directly into the UniForum SA bank account with reference DNS-NameOfDelegate or paid by cheque directly at the UniForum SA offices.\r\n\r\nPlease fax proof of payment to 080 314 0088, or alternately email proof of payment to accounts@co.za for attention Lizette Els.\r\n\r\nThe training course starts at 9h00 and finishes at 17h00.\r\n\r\nNotes, computer terminals, refreshments and lunch will be provided. ',2008,'September','Y','/var/www/html/data/2008/','2020-12-18 17:34:50','Administrative Account','2008-09-08 11:45:23',NULL,'N',NULL,'no','no',0,0,-33.922401,18.415661),(421,6,'NANOG 45','2009-01-25','2009-01-28','http://text.nanog.org/meetings/nanog45/','http://www.nanog.org/meetings/nanog45/hotel.php','do','Santo Domingo','Latin America/Caribbean islands','North America','Global','English','Spanish','','','Renaissance Jaragua Hotel','','','Join us at NANOG45\r\n\r\nNANOG will make its first trip to the Dominican Republic in January 2009, and we hope you can join us in the Caribbean! NANOG45 will take place in t