17.966669,102.599998),(1849,893,'Leadership &amp; People Management Course','2020-03-03','2020-03-06','https://mdf.nl/leadership-and-people-management-20','','vn','Hanoi','Asia/Australia/Pacific','','','English',NULL,NULL,'','','Nguyen Thanh Thuy','mdfasia@mdf.nl ','Why this course?\r\nThis Leadership and People Management \r\ntraining course is designed to support \r\nformal or informal leaders, to be more \r\nauthentic in their transactions and develop \r\nbehaviours that enable the individual and \r\nthe organisation to perform at the highest \r\nlevel. Be prepared to look inwards as well \r\nas outwards. Especially important for those \r\nfacing challenges in leading others. You will \r\ndevelop your leadership and walk away \r\nwith a practical management toolkit\r\n\r\nCourse objectives\r\nBy the end of this course, you will:\r\n√¢‚Ç¨¬¢	Know more about yourself as a person \r\nand a leader, including: specific strengths \r\nand what is holding you back\r\n√¢‚Ç¨¬¢	Be aware of different styles of \r\nleadership, what type of leader you are and \r\nhow you can develop further\r\n√¢‚Ç¨¬¢	 Have sharpened practical skills in \r\nleading and managing others (feedback, \r\ncoaching, team work, conflict management, \r\n&amp; resistance)\r\n√¢‚Ç¨¬¢	Understand diversity and cultural \r\nissues in leadership\r\n\r\nWho should join?\r\nThis course is designed for formal &amp; \r\ninformal leaders, managers at all levels and \r\nfor those who are aspiring to a leadership \r\nposition &amp; especially those facing \r\nchallenges in leading others.\r\n\r\nCourse agenda\r\nDay 1: Personal leadership challenges\r\nWhat is leadership vs management, myths \r\n&amp; reality\r\nLeadership in relation to culture, diversity &amp; \r\ngender\r\nRecognising your personality preferences\r\n\r\nDay 2: Building &amp; earning trust\r\nAcknowledging your strengths &amp; \r\nweaknesses\r\nBeing self-accountable &amp; articulating your \r\npersonal vision\r\n\r\nDay 3: Leading in different si