,'Takes place on 11th August from\r\n13:00 - 15:00 UTC',2020,'August','Y','/var/www/sites/data/2020/','2020-09-28 15:47:16','Denesh Bhabuta','2020-06-29 16:12:41','denesh@uknof.org.uk','N',NULL,'no','no',0,1,0.000000,0.000000),(1934,893,'Advocacy and Policy Influencing (online)','2020-08-03','2020-08-06','https://mdf.nl/advocacy-and-policy-influencing-online','https://mdf.nl','','','','','','English',NULL,NULL,'','Online','https://mdf.nl','mdfasia@mdf.nl','Advocacy &amp;amp; Policy Influencing \r\n(Online)\r\nInfluence decision-makers and \r\ncommunicate the evidence\r\nWhy this course?\r\nUnderstand how you can influence a \r\npolicy process. From first stages to final \r\nimplementation. It could\r\nbe your core business or an intrinsic \r\npart of your organisation. Obtain a \r\nbroad set of tools to plan\r\neffective advocacy strategies. Conduct \r\nactions with well-framed messages, and \r\ncreate coherent paths\r\nwith your allies for powerful joint \r\ninterventions. Learn how to monitor \r\nadvocacy results.\r\nCourse objectives\r\nBy the end of this course, you will:\r\n√Ø‚Äö¬∑ Understand how to embed advocacy \r\nactions in your organisation√¢‚Ç¨‚Ñ¢s plans\r\n√Ø‚Äö¬∑ Use practical tools and methods to \r\nplan, prepare, implement and evaluate \r\nadvocacy initiatives\r\n√Ø‚Äö¬∑ Analyse stakeholders and policy \r\ncontext\r\n√Ø‚Äö¬∑ Gain insight into building strong \r\ncoalitions, select your political targets, \r\nframe your messages in\r\nconvincing ways\r\n√Ø‚Äö¬∑ Practice how to conduct influential \r\nlobby meetings\r\n√Ø‚Äö¬∑ Learn how to monitor advocacy \r\nresults\r\nWho should join?\r\nYou are a professional engaged in \r\nadvocacy, civil society capacity building, \r\ngovernance or transparency\r\nprogrammes. You may represent a \r\nnetwork, an alliance, an association or a \r\ntrade union. You defend the\r\ninterests of many or promote rights for \r\nyour target groups.\r\nMeet your trainer\r\nMr. Koen Toonen\r\nSenior Trainer/Consultant\r\nMDF Training &amp;amp; Consutancy, \r\nVietnam Office\r\nEmail: kto@mdf.nl\r\nMr. Toonen is senior trainer of MDF \r\nVietnam office. Koen also has over 20 \r\nyears of development\r\nexperience at the UN. He was involved \r\nin managing the UNDP-UNEP Poverty \r\nEnvironment Partnership.\r\nHe is an all-round development expert \r\nand trainer in Results-Based \r\nManagement, Monitoring and\r\nEvaluation, Advocacy and Policy \r\nInfluencing, Network Management, \r\nMulti-stakeholder Partnerships,\r\nSustainability Planning, Institutional \r\nDevelopment and Organizational \r\nStrengthening, notably for poverty\r\nalleviation and environmental \r\nmanagement.\r\nMs. Ger Roebeling\r\nSenior Trainer/Consultant\r\nMDF Training &amp;amp; Consultancy, \r\nNetherlands Office\r\n\r\nEmail: GR@mdf.nl\r\nMs. Ger Roebeling has a longstanding \r\ncareer in International Cooperation with \r\nexperience in the field,\r\nand 20 years in different management \r\npositions (programme management, \r\nprogramme and general\r\ndirector) in International organisations, \r\nranging from the Netherlands to Africa, \r\nAsia, Latin America and\r\nEastern Europa &amp;amp; Caucasus, and \r\nMENA region. She is the founder of \r\nseveral policy networks based on\r\nTrade, Food Security, WASH up to EU, \r\nUN and World Trade Organisation \r\nlevels and she managed\r\nworldwide multi stakeholder \r\npartnerships and development \r\nprogrammes. Her policy interventions \r\nhave\r\nled to the elimination of agricultural \r\nsubsidies stopping the dumping of Food \r\nAid. She joined MDF in\r\n2008 and became one of the first \r\ninterim and change managers, \r\ndeveloped training courses on\r\nAdvocacy and Policy Influencing, \r\nPartnership &amp;amp; Network \r\nmanagement, Security and Gender, and\r\nLeadership &amp;amp; Coaching.\r\nMs. Roebeling is an experienced and \r\ninspiring advisor, facilitator, coach and \r\ntrainer. Her creative\r\nmethods are of a visionary and \r\ninteractive nature, using mutual \r\nexchange of experiences as an\r\nimportant vehicle for co-creation. She \r\napplies theoretical concepts and tools in \r\na practical way in\r\nworkshops and learning events by using \r\na range of different interactive learning \r\nmethods, such as case\r\nstudies, focused conversation, \r\nindividual reflection, group work, \r\nfeedback, role plays, debates, and\r\nsimulations. Ms. Roebeling is a certified \r\nsystemic coach for organisations and \r\nnetworks, for which she\r\nhorses are playing a role regularly.\r\nEssential Information\r\nTime: 3 √¢‚Ç¨‚Äú 6 August 2020 (8 sessions \r\nduring 4 days, 2 sessions each day, 1.5 \r\nhours/session)\r\nCourse fee: 825 EUR (excluding tax)\r\nRegistration deadline: 27 July 2020\r\nRegistration: visit our course page here\r\nSpecial offers\r\n5% early bird discount to participants \r\nwho completed their payments by the \r\nend of .\r\n10% discount to MDF alumni who \r\nattended an MDF course within the past \r\n2 years\r\n1 free place for a group of 6 \r\nregistrations from the same organization\r\nContact us\r\nMDF Asia, Vietnam Office\r\nAdd: Room 501, A1 building, Van Phuc \r\nDiplomatic Compound,\r\n298 Kim Ma Street, Ba Dinh District, \r\nHanoi, Vietnam\r\nEmail: mdfasia@mdf.nl\r\nPhone: +84 (0)24 6258 4438',2020,'August','Y','/var/www/sites/data/2020/','2020-06-30 06:13:23','MDF  Asia','2020-06-29 23:13:23',NULL,'N',NULL,'no','on',0,0,0.000000,0.000000),(1935,893,'Online training course √¢‚Ç¨≈ìWRITING WINNING PROPOSALS√¢‚Ç¨¬ù','2020-08-11','2020-08-14','https://mdf.nl/writing-winning-proposals-online','https://mdf.nl','','','','','','English',NULL,NULL,'','Online','Mr. Tung Nguyen','mdfasia@mdf.nl','Online training course √¢‚Ç¨≈ìWRITING \r\nWINNING PROPOSALS√¢‚Ç¨¬ù\r\nWe are living in an increasingly \r\ndigitalised and globalised world. Why \r\nnot use this for the best?\r\nIn 2014, MDF started our first blended \r\ncourse in which traditional face-to-face \r\ntraining is combined with\r\nonline sessions. Over years, our \r\nONLINE TRAINING SERVICE, which \r\nallows remote learning with the same\r\nquality and more flexible time, has been \r\nsuccessfully developed and recognized.\r\nOnline learning is so much more than \r\nsharing resources online! It requires a \r\ndiversified set of tools,\r\nskills and pedagogic insight to design \r\ninteractive and facilitated online courses \r\nin the form of either\r\nvirtual classrooms or individual \r\ncoaching session.\r\nSo, there is no need for any interruption \r\nin your career and self development, \r\ndespite Covid-19\r\npandemic! Join MDF Asia online \r\ntraining √¢‚Ç¨≈ìWriting Winning Proposals√¢‚Ç¨¬ù this \r\nAugust and enjoy your\r\nvirtual learning experience. Here is the \r\ncourse information:\r\nWhy you should attend the course?\r\n√Ø‚Äö¬∑ Saving travel time &amp; costs\r\n√Ø‚Äö¬∑ Minimized interruption to your work\r\n√Ø‚Äö¬∑ Maximize your use of time\r\n√Ø‚Äö¬∑ Access to MDF international training \r\nfrom anywhere\r\n√Ø‚Äö¬∑ More flexible training schedule\r\n√Ø‚Äö¬∑ Free access to MDF online resources\r\n√Ø‚Äö¬∑ More of your staff can join at once\r\n√Ø‚Äö¬∑ Easily-monitored progress report\r\n√Ø‚Äö¬∑ Information retention\r\n√Ø‚Äö¬∑ No risk of Covid-19!\r\nCourse objectives\r\nBy the end of the course, you will:\r\n√Ø‚Äö¬∑ Have learned to match your unique \r\nproposal idea and added value with \r\nfunders√¢‚Ç¨‚Ñ¢ needs\r\n√Ø‚Äö¬∑ Make sound GO / NO GO decisions \r\non opportunities\r\n√Ø‚Äö¬∑ Know how to bring logic and structure \r\nto your proposal and improve the writing \r\nprocess\r\n√Ø‚Äö¬∑ Understand the appraisal procedures \r\nand criteria that will be used to evaluate \r\nyour proposal\r\n√Ø‚Äö¬∑ Have practised &amp; raised your \r\nconfidence in proposal writing\r\n\r\nEssential information\r\n√Ø‚Äö¬∑ Time: 11 √¢‚Ç¨‚Äú 14 August 2020\r\n√Ø‚Äö¬∑ 8 sessions in total; 2 session/day; 1.5 \r\nhours/session\r\n√Ø‚Äö¬∑ Training platform: Zoom\r\n√Ø‚Äö¬∑ Course fee: 825 EUR (excluding tax)\r\n√