n \r\nstudies. Rudolf is extensively involved in \r\ndesigning online\r\nmodules for blended learning \r\ntrajectories (e.g.using Moodle, H5P, \r\nMURAL), and is an expert in using\r\nonline M&amp;E tools (e.g. \r\nKobotoolbox, SurveyMonkey, \r\nSprockler).\r\nContact us\r\nMDF Asia, Vietnam Office\r\nAdd: Room 501, A1 Building, Van Phuc \r\nDiplomatic Compound\r\n298 Kim Ma Street, Ba Dinh District, \r\nHanoi\r\nTel: +84 (0) 24 6258 4438\r\nEmail: mdfasia@mdf.nl',2020,'August','Y','/var/www/sites/data/2020/','2020-06-30 06:25:12','MDF  Asia','2020-06-29 23:25:12',NULL,'N',NULL,'no','on',0,0,0.000000,0.000000),(1937,12,'AIS 2020','2020-09-14','2020-09-18','https://2020.internetsummit.africa/en/','','','','Africa','','','English',NULL,NULL,'','','','','',2020,'September','Y','/var/www/sites/data/2020/','2020-09-28 15:47:16','Philip Smith','2020-07-16 20:41:34',NULL,'N',NULL,'no','no',0,1,0.000000,0.000000),(1938,893,'Advocacy and Policy Influencing (Online course)','2020-08-03','2020-08-13','https://mdf.nl/advocacy-and-policy-influencing-online','https://www.facebook.com/events/561895314500082/','vn','Hanoi','Asia/Australia/Pacific','','','English',NULL,NULL,'','Online','Ms. Thuy Do','mdfasia@mdf.nl','Why this course?\r\n\r\nYou are a professional engaged in \r\nadvocacy, civil society capacity building, \r\ngovernance or transparency \r\nprogrammes. You may represent a \r\nnetwork, an alliance, an association or a \r\ntrade-union. You defend the interests of \r\nmany or promote rights for your target \r\ngroups. This course will assist you in \r\nunderstanding how you can influence a \r\npolicy process. From the first stages to \r\nfinal implementation. Obtain a broad set \r\nof tools to plan effective advocacy \r\nstrategies. Conduct actions with well-\r\nframed messages, and create coherent \r\npaths with your allies for powerful joint \r\ninterventions. Learn how to monitor \r\nadvocacy results.\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\nCourse Objectives\r\n\r\nUnderstand how to embed advocacy \r\nactions in your organization√¢‚Ç¨‚Ñ¢s plans\r\nUse practical tools and methods to plan, \r\nprepare, implement and evaluate \r\nadvocacy initiatives\r\nAnalyse stakeholders and policy context\r\nGain insight into building strong \r\ncoalitions, select your political targets, \r\nframe your messages in convincing \r\nways\r\nPractice how to conduct influential lobby \r\nmeetings\r\nLearn how to monitor advocacy results\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\nCourse Agenda\r\n\r\nThis course is offered over a 4-day \r\nperiod, involving 8 sessions which lasts \r\n1.5 hours each (2 sessions per day). \r\nThe course is based on a participatory, \r\nactive learning approach with a \r\ncombination of guided virtual classroom \r\nand learning at your pace. The following \r\ntopics will be covered in the course, \r\nwhich might be further adjusted to suit \r\nparticipants√¢‚Ç¨‚Ñ¢ training needs:\r\n\r\nCONCEPTS &amp; PRINCIPLES\r\nWelcome and introduction\r\nPolicy Influencing and Advocacy \r\nconcepts, Policy Influencing Cycle\r\nCLASP principles\r\nTheory of Change\r\n\r\nANALYSING THE CONTEXT\r\nPolicy mapping\r\nSituation analysis / PESTLE analysis\r\nStakeholder Analysis √¢‚Ç¨‚Äú Actor Mapping\r\nNetwork alliances and dynamics\r\n\r\nSKILL BUILDING\r\nCommunications: framing the message\r\nSkills building: elevator pitch\r\nWin-win negotiations\r\nSkills building: practise a lobby meeting\r\n\r\nDESIGNING CAMPAIGNS AND \r\nMONITORING RESULTS\r\nMonitoring results: Outcome Harvesting\r\nSocial Media for Advocacy\r\nDesigning your advocacy campaign\r\nEvaluation and certification\r\n\r\n\r\nMEET YOUR TRAINERS\r\nKoen Walter Toonen\r\nSenior Trainer/Consultant (MDF \r\nVietnam)\r\nMr. Toonen is senior trainer of MDF \r\nVietnam office. Koen also has over 20 \r\nyears of development experience at the \r\nUN. He was involved in managing the \r\nUNDP-UNEP Poverty Environment \r\nPartnership. He is an all-round \r\ndevelopment expert and trainer.\r\n\r\nGer Roebeling\r\nSenior Trainer/Consul