s or mobilise new resources for \r\nyour organisation. You want to \r\ndemonstrate your added value but are \r\nfacing stiff competition. This course will \r\nhelp you learn how to write a proposal \r\nthat stands out. We believe that writing a \r\nconvincing and attractive proposal is \r\nsomething we all can learn.\r\n\r\n\r\nCourse Objectives\r\n\r\nLearn to match your unique proposal \r\nidea and added value with funders√¢‚Ç¨‚Ñ¢ \r\nneeds\r\nMake sound GO / NO GO decisions on \r\nopportunities\r\nKnow how to bring logic and structure to \r\nyour proposal and improve the writing \r\nprocess\r\nUnderstand the appraisal procedures \r\nand criteria that will be used to evaluate \r\nyour proposal\r\nPractise and raise your confidence in \r\nproposal writing\r\n\r\n\r\nCourse Agenda\r\n\r\nThis course is offered over a 4-day \r\nperiod, involving 8 sessions which lasts \r\n1.5 hours each (2 sessions per day). \r\nThe course is based on a participatory, \r\nactive learning approach with a \r\ncombination of guided virtual classroom \r\nand learning at your pace. The following \r\ntopics will be covered in the course, \r\nwhich might be further adjusted to suit \r\nparticipants√¢‚Ç¨‚Ñ¢ training needs:\r\n\r\nDAY 1\r\nIntroduction, objectives and program\r\nKnow your organization\r\nKnow your Donor grants\r\nGo/No-go decisions\r\n\r\nDAY 2\r\nKnow your planning: The writing process\r\nStructure your proposal\r\nProposal content: Mind mapping\r\nTranslating guidelines into an \r\nintervention\r\n\r\nDAY 3\r\nHow to be convincing and persuasive\r\nParagraph writing\r\nFundamentals of good writing\r\nCrafting the concept note\r\n\r\nDAY 4\r\nKnow your pitch\r\nAppraisal procedure\r\nAssessment of the proposals\r\nPersonal action plan\r\nEvaluation and closing\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\nMEET YOUR TRAINERS\r\nSusanne van Lieshout\r\nSenior Trainer/Consultant\r\nDirector of MDF Kenya\r\nMs. Van Lieshout has over 20 years of \r\nexperience in the overseas development \r\nsector working wit